&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;107&quot; data-end=&quot;729&quot;&gt;At Fireworks, we’re building the future of generative AI infrastructure. Our platform delivers the highest-quality models with the fastest and most scalable inference in the industry. We’ve been independently benchmarked as the leader in LLM inference speed and are driving cutting-edge innovation through projects like our own function calling and multimodal models. Fireworks is a Series C company valued at $4 billion and backed by top investors including Benchmark, Sequoia, Lightspeed, Index, and Evantic. We’re an ambitious, collaborative team of builders, founded by veterans of Meta PyTorch and Google Vertex AI.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;The Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a strategic and hands-on Senior Recruiter to join our growing team and help fuel our next phase of growth. In this role, you’ll partner closely with hiring managers and cross-functional teams to lead full-cycle recruitment for a variety of roles across Engineering, Product, Marketing, and Sales. You’ll play a key role in shaping the hiring strategy, enhancing candidate experience, and building strong talent pipelines as we scale rapidly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Key Responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and manage full-cycle recruitment across multiple functions, with a focus on quality, speed, and candidate experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with hiring managers to understand hiring needs, craft job descriptions, calibrate on candidate profiles, and drive hiring strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively source and engage high-quality candidates through multiple channels, including direct outreach, networking, referrals, and platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain talent mapping and pipelines for key roles and future needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with HRBPs, Compensation, and other People functions to align on talent strategies, role design, and market insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide market intelligence and data-driven recommendations to influence hiring plans and organizational growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help optimize recruiting operations, leveraging ATS and other tools to ensure a smooth and scalable process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion a diverse, inclusive, and equitable hiring process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Minimum Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of hands-on recruiting experience, ideally in fast-paced or high-growth environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record recruiting across technical and/or non-technical roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to partner with founders, hiring managers, and executives to shape and influence hiring strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong sourcing and candidate engagement skills, with a knack for identifying top talent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work with urgency while maintaining high quality standards and thoughtful candidate experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience scaling talent teams or organizations in startup or hypergrowth environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with compensation structures and equity benchmarking in early-stage startups.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Talent Operations to implement and optimize recruiting tools, systems, and workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with applicant tracking systems (ATS) like Greenhouse, and leveraging them for end-to-end recruitment lifecycle management.&lt;/li&gt;
