&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;107&quot; data-end=&quot;729&quot;&gt;At Fireworks, we’re building the future of generative AI infrastructure. Our platform delivers the highest-quality models with the fastest and most scalable inference in the industry. We’ve been independently benchmarked as the leader in LLM inference speed and are driving cutting-edge innovation through projects like our own function calling and multimodal models. Fireworks is a Series C company valued at $4 billion and backed by top investors including Benchmark, Sequoia, Lightspeed, Index, and Evantic. We’re an ambitious, collaborative team of builders, founded by veterans of Meta PyTorch and Google Vertex AI.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finance and Business Operations at Fireworks sits at the heart of how we scale — from the infrastructure powering our inference cloud to the financial cadence driving company-wide decisions. We work closely with engineering, product, and leadership to make smart, fast bets with our resources. This is a team where rigor meets speed, and where your work will directly shape how one of the most important infrastructure companies in AI grows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re hiring a Sr. Manager or Director of Strategic Finance to lead infrastructure capacity and financial planning, and serve as the finance partner to our Engineering and Product teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll be the financial architect behind how we invest in GPUs and infrastructure — the backbone of everything we do. Beyond the modeling, you&#39;ll be embedded with our engineering and product teams, helping them make better decisions faster by bringing financial rigor to roadmap tradeoffs, headcount planning, and strategic investments. This is a role for someone equally comfortable in a spreadsheet and in a room full of engineers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is based in our San Mateo, CA office on a hybrid schedule.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own capacity planning across compute infrastructure — modeling GPU, storage, and networking needs against current and projected demand&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead financial planning for infrastructure investments, including scenario modeling, vendor analysis, and cost optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary finance business partner to Engineering and Product — supporting roadmap prioritization, investment tradeoffs, and resource allocation decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop deep fluency in contract structures and pricing to identify and capture optimization opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain financial models that connect infrastructure spend to business outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex technical plans into clear financial frameworks that inform executive decision-making&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay current on compute market trends and competitive dynamics to sharpen our infrastructure strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in strategic finance, FP&amp;amp;A, investment banking, or private equity, with 3–4+ years in a finance operating role at a high-growth technology company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience as a finance business partner to engineering or product teams — you know how to build trust with technical stakeholders and make yourself indispensable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong grasp of cloud and compute infrastructure economics — you understand how GPU capacity, utilization, and pricing models actually work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional financial modeling skills; you can build from scratch and work comfortably under ambiguity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clear, confident communicator — equally effective presenting to engineers, product leaders, and the C-suite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A bias for action and a track record of driving outcomes under ambitious timelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Finance, Economics, Engineering, or a related field; MBA a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Fireworks AI?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
